  "text": "It follows that block Jacobi converges if and only if block upper-and lower-triangular preconditioners, with diagonal blocks given by A 11 and A 22 , both converge. Furthermore, the expected number of iterations of block Jacobi to converge to a given tolerance are approximately double that of the equivalent block-triangular preconditioning, give or take some independent constant factor (e.g., A −1 11 A 12 ) from the fixedpoint operators. A similar result is later shown for preconditioning Krylov methods with block Jacobi (see Theorem 3.6) . This relation of twice as many iterations for Jacobi/block-diagonal preconditioning has been noted or observed a number of times, perhaps originally in [CITATION_1] where MINRES/GMRES are proven to stall every other iteration on saddle-point problems.",
